(200, 0, 0, '2024-05', 'BSIT-NS', 'Capstone', 'A Proposed SD-WAN Architecture Using Cloud-Delivered Security Solutions for Nextrade Philippines Inc.', 'Karl Matthew P. Palmaira - Jess Andrew I. Reguine - Exequiel Mico U. Sales', '', 'The researchers of this Capstone Project have worked in addressing the existing issues and concerns in network security for NexTrade Philippines Inc. The effectiveness and efficiency of the network security system is required for a company in order to reduce a company\'s liabilities, insurance, compensation, and other social security costs to stakeholders in the event of it experiencing a network attack or failure. Organizations should also take into consideration of improving its revenue while lowering the operational costs to utilize the company\'s budget effectively. To further asses the problems and its solutions, an interview was conducted together with looking up various studies regarding the implementation of SD-WAN or Software-Defined Wide Area Network and its features that focuses on security to an organization\'s network infrastructure. In order to address the issues in the increase of latency and stability that comes with internet connections that are long distance, the researchers proposed a SD-WAN architecture. Policies under server management were also proposed by the researchers in order to ensure user and device compliance to the organization\'s respective policies and to ensure security within the local area network of the company\'s offices. The time limit and requirements posed challenges and difficulties to the researchers of this capstone project. The researchers then concluded that organizations that have a main branch and satellite branches must have proper ', 'Software-Defined Wide Area Network (SD-WAN), Next Generation Firewall (NGFW), Cloud Access Security Broker (CASB), Zero-Trust Network Approach (ZTNA),'),
(201, 0, 0, '2024-05', 'BSCS-AD', 'Thesis', 'Development of TAICHNO: An Educational Assessment Tool for Taijiquan\'s Stance with Real-time Accuracy and Feedback Utilizing Blaze Pose Mediapipe Algo', 'Reynan M. Ersolada - John Simon M. Legaspi - Honey Lei B. Lizardo - Christine Joy B. Pelayo - Ronnielyn S. Valenzuela', '', 'This research paper introduces the development of a web-based application TAICHNO, an educational assessment tool designed to provide real-time accuracy and feedback on Taijiquan stances. TAICHNO utilizes MediaPipe\'s BlazePose algorithm, a deep learning- based pose estimation model, to analyze the user\'s posture during stance training. The system provides visual feedback on the users in comparison to ideal Taijiquan stance parameters. This real-time assessment can enhance learning efficiency and promote accurate stance acquisition for Taijiquan practitioners. TAICHNO bridges the gap by harnessing advanced technology, specifically the BlazePose MediaPipe algorithm, to offer real-time assessment and feedback on stances. The development approach utilized Agile Data Science and a data-driven approach to application development. The researchers used ISO 25010 standards to evaluate the web application in the form of a survey questionnaire. Beyond TAICHNO, the paper studied about traditional Chinese mind-body exercise, emphasizes proper stance for balance, stability and demands both physical alignment and mental focus. This study delves into the nuanced intricacies of eight traditional stances: Horse Stance (Ma Bu), Bow-Arrow Stance (Gong JianBu), Sitting on Crossed Legs Stance (Zuo Pan Bu), Four-Six Stance (Si Liu Bu), Tame the Tiger Stance (Fu Hu Bu), False Stance (Xuan Ji Bu or Xu Bu), Golden Rooster Standing on One Leg Stance (Jin Gi Du Li), and Squat Stance Zuo Dun). Through a ', 'Taijiquan, MediaPipe Algorithm, Human Pose Estimation, Confusion Matrix, FeedForward Neural Network, BlazePose'),
(202, 0, 0, '2024-05', 'BSCS-AD', 'Thesis', 'Development of TAGA-TSEK: An Educational Grammar Checker Tool for Pokus Ng Pandiwa Explored Using Distilbert Algorithm', 'Ryan Jay M. Acosta - Matthew D. Bierneza - Jonny P. Sagloria - Jeimee Nicole P. Salvador - Shaina V. Vinoya', '', 'This study investigated the morphological transfer of Tagalog grammar with a focus on Pokus ng Pandiwa using the DistilBERT method. To improve language accuracy and competency in Tagalog, the study intended to create and develop an educational grammar checker tool in Pokus ng Pandiwa that reliably recognized these grammar rules. The educational tool has the following features: grammar checker, modules, quizzes, and games for Filipino teachers and students. Artificial intelligence sentences generated, validated, and corrected by professionals in the field were used in the study to train the DistilBERT algorithm. The study\'s focus had been strictly on Pokus ng Pandiwa, leaving out other grammatical conventions and terms that were not Tagalog. The preparation of the Tagalog corpus, application of appropriate grammatical rules, and use of DistilBERT for analysis were all part of the research strategy. Precision, Recall, and Fl score were used for training evaluation and ISO 25010 was used to evaluate the system. Furthermore, the results of actual testing proved that the developed educational grammar checker tool was able to enhance language accuracy and proficiency in Pokus ng\nPandiwa resulting in an overall accuracy of 86%.', 'Natural Language Processing, Grammar Checking, DistilBERT, Tagalog language, Pokus ng Pandiwa.'),
(203, 0, 0, '2024-05', 'BSCS-AD', 'Thesis', 'Development of APYRO: Smart Attendance System for Hyflex Learning in Higher Education Using Convolutional Neural Network Algorithm', 'Jan Kent Amiel O. Diego - Jilbert P Lim - Khrizza C. Persona - Leonardo G. Timkang Jr. - Patrick J. Etesam', '', 'Studies revolving around attendance systems have been an enduring focus of research. Over the past decade, various solutions have been proposed, each aiming to enhance efficiency and reduce time consumption. However, each individual system has its own flaws and errors. With the emergence of hyflex learning and the social issues it presents in onsite and virtual classes, the lack of familiarity can lead to challenges in effectively tracking attendance and addressing the specific needs of this environment. This study introduces a new approach to attendance systems in hyflex learning using modern techniques,\nspecifically machine learning. The researchers utilized the pre-trained SSD MobileNet V1, a convolutional neural network-based model, to create a face recognition model by applying transfer learning techniques. During the development of the model, face images and face annotations were gathered as part of the data collection process serving as the target training data for validation and testing. After the model was developed, the researchers created a web application called APyro using the agile methodology approach and implemented the trained model along with the developed system. The system and the models were evaluated using different metrics. The overall outcome of the system addressed specific social issues in the hyflex modality, offering a potential solution to some challenges faced in attendance tracking in this setting.', 'Hyflex learning, SSD MobileNet V1, transfer learning, convolutional neural network, agile methodology, model evaluation.'),
(204, 0, 0, '2024-05', 'BSCS-AD', 'Thesis', 'Development of AISTILO: A System for Preserving Philippine Artistic Heritage Through Neural Style Transfer Techniques with Domain Adaptation', 'Jose Renan A. Gasidan - Jose B. Gayares III, Angel Kaye B. Macatuhay - Novem Jan Dzel L. Sayman - Marielle M. Zabala', '', 'Arts and culture are the least explored fields in computer vision and machine learning studies. This research addresses the challenge of preserving the art and culture of the Philippines. Implementing Neural Style Transfer and VGG 19, a computer vision model, the study develops a method for integrating Filipino art styles into digital images through the AISTILO application. Quality evaluation of generated images was conducted using two metrics: Learned Perceptual Image Patch SimilarityLPIPS) and Human Eye Perceptual Evaluation (HYPE), which showed an inverse relationship. The style transfer model demonstrated consistent performance in both metrics. However, with a T-statistics of 4.50 and a P-value of 0.02 on Paired T-test the evaluation of two metrics have statistically significant differences. Further assessment of the AISTILO app based on ISO 25010 standards for functionality, performance and security obtained high user satisfaction scores: 3.45 for functional suitability, 3.29 for performance efficiency and 3.36 for security which all interpret to \"Strongly agree\". While the study confirms the help of technology in cultural preservation, it also presents the need for continued improvement and long term evaluation. High app ratings show Filipinos support digital takes on tradition, which could help keep Filipino culture alive for future generations..', 'Style transfer, Domain adaptation, Cultural Artistic Heritage, Transfer Learning'),
(205, 0, 0, '2024-05', 'BSCS-AD', 'Thesis', 'TRAINAPAW: Development of Dog Training Recommender Application with Hybrid Filtering Techniques for Fun & Wild Dog Training Services and Rehabilitatio', 'Jessie Q. Chua - Ghen Paul D. Dulin - John Patrick C. Isidoro - Webster III D. Tolosa - Jenelia Rose N. Bueno', '', 'This thesis study presents TrainaPaw, a mobile application that provides dog owners with personalized training recommendations. By examining its design, user experience, and performance, the study delves into the system architecture, which integrates K-Nearest Neighbors, content-based filtering, and collaborative filtering techniques to generate training recommendations based on user input and a database of training content. The study further analyzes survey findings, which reveal user preferences and suggest improvements such as more detailed trainer profiles, a resource library for dog training materials, and enhanced announcements and reviews. Finally, the study concludes with an ISO 25010 assessment of TrainaPaw to evaluate its functionality, user experience, and security features. The researchers found that the combination of the K-Nearest Neighbors algorithm and hybrid filtering techniques was highly effective in recommending personalized dog training, achieving a precision of 90.38%, recall of 88.83%, accuracy of 88.83%, and an F1 score of 88.35%. This application aims to significantly enhance dog owner engagement by providing porsonalized recommendations and fostering a deeper understanding of the importance of dog training. By establishing clear boundaries, facilitating social connections, and strengthening the bond between dogs and their owners, effective training benefits both human and canine companions.', 'Dog Training Recommender System, Hybrid Filtering, Collaborative Filtering, Content-Based Filtering, K-Nearest Neighbors.'),
(206, 0, 0, '2024-05', 'BSCS-AD', 'Thesis', 'Peso Masters: An Educational Card Game Application in Financial Literacy for Kids Using Fisher-yates Algorithm and Greedy Algorithm', 'Edrianne Loise A. Agrava - Jed Angeli C. Cleofe - Mark Genesis S. Dumayas', '', 'Financial literacy involves the ability to properly manage personal finances, including earning, saving, spending, borrowing, and protecting assets. Being skilled in making wise financial decisions contributes to financial stability and freedom. This study focuses on applying the Fisher-Yates Algorithm for shuffling and randomizing a deck of cards and the Greedy Algorithm to aid decision-making in the game \"Peso Masters.\" \"Peso Masters\" is a 2D educational game developed in Unity to teach basic financial literacy concepts to children aged 8 to 9 years old. The Agile Methodology was used in software development, and various research designs were adopted, including developmental and descriptive (descriptive evaluative) research methodologies and simple random sampling methods. After developing the game, the researchers conducted an evaluation targeting children aged 8 to 9 years old. The evaluation was done online; the game was uploaded to itch.io, and survey questions were distributed via Google Forms. Most respondents were children in the target age group, and the game received the highest rating for functional suitability. However, only a few respondents provided feedback and suggestions for improvement.\nThe results indicate the game\'s credibility, suggesting that with some improvements, it could effectively teach financial literacy to children aged 8 to 9 years old.', 'Financial literacy, Fisher Yates Algorithm, Greedy Algorithm, Educational Game, Card Game'),
(207, 0, 0, '2024-04', 'BSCS-AD', 'Thesis', 'Development of Chrono Clash: A Strategic Board Game Utilizing K-nearest Neighbors and Minimax Algorithm for Possible Game Players Movement', 'Emmanuel Christian D. Dalida - Nikko B. Dulay - Michael Dave C. Garcia - Juztin Rafhael C. Gonatice - Fernan R. Retardo', '', 'This thesis explores the transition of the traditional board game to digital, focusing on the development of Chrono Clash, a mobile game that applies algorithms to enhance player engagement and tactical skills. Utilizing a developmental research approach, the game underwent iterative design based on player feedback, supported by comprehensive planning, and literature review. Also, the game adopted a Game Development Life Cycle (GDLC) methodology to develop the game. The incorporation of k-nearest neighbors and minimax algorithm in gameplay resulted in significant improvements in player\nengagement and critical thinking skills. While the dataset is currently limited, the KNN algorithm performs well in the confusion matrix, achieving a balanced accuracy of\naround 70% (weighted average of precision, recall, and F1-score). Moreover, minimax with pruning offers a significant advantage by creating game outcome analysis, the researchers concluded that depth suggests well during the testing. Games played using this algorithm exhibit fewer player moves and shorter overall match times compared to games without Minimax. An evaluation of the game using ISO-25010 resulted in a score of 4.04, indicating high marks in functionality, performance, flexibility, and interaction. =Overall, players have a positive impression of the game\'s design, and features suggest a strong potential for market success.', 'Decision Tree, K-Nearest Neighbor, Minimax Algorithm, Minimax with Pruning, Confusion Matrix, ISO-25010, Game Development Life Cycle (GDLC)'),
(208, 0, 0, '2024-05', 'BSCS-AD', 'Thesis', 'ITHINK: Implementation of Pattern Matching Algorithm in the Development of Game Based Learning Python Tutorial for Beginners', 'Ed Dominic T. Bariso - Carlo Rhegs F. Cambel - Manuel G. Kosca Jr. - Jayson B. Narce', '', '', ''),
(209, 0, 0, '2024-05', 'BSCS-AD', 'Thesis', 'Development of UMEP: An Augmented Reality Wayfinding Digitalizing the Health and Physical Science Building Evacuation Plan Using A* Algorithm and Indo', 'Ranger C. Enoja - Aldrian B. Escarlan - Sheerymae P. Curameng - Ezequel B. Lingal - Francisco A. Bleza', '', 'This research investigates the effectiveness of the University of Makati Evacuation Plan (UMEP), an Augmented Reality (AR) wayfinding application designed to enhance emergency preparedness within the university\'s Health and Physical Science Building. UMEP leverages AR technology, the A* pathfinding algorithm, and a QR code-based Indoor Positioning System (IPS) to guide users during evacuation drills. It offers real-time navigation by pinpointing the shortest escape route and tracking user location. The study employs a mixed-methods approach, combining a descriptive review of existing evacuation plan practices and developmental approach that follows AGILE methodology for building UMEP application. The purposive sampling technique participated by 120 students from the College of Computing and Information Sciences (CCIS). Data collection was facilitated through an ISO 25010-compliant user-survey questionnaire, with statistical analysis providing insights into UMEP\'s usability and effectiveness. Functional testing verified the application\'s components, with detailed metrics demonstrating the successful implementation and performance of the AR, A* algorithm, and IPS features. While the study identified limitations, user feedback indicated positive perceptions. UMEP received positive feedback for its functionality, usability, reliability, efficiency, and compatibility. This suggests UMEP can be a valuable tool for emergency preparedness training. Its engaging features and user-frie', 'A* Algorithm, Augmented Reality, Evacuation Plan, Indoor Positioning System, QR code'),
(210, 0, 0, '2024-05', 'BSCS-AD', 'Thesis', 'Development of College Degree Program Recommender System for Incoming Freshmen Students Using Classification Technique', 'Emmanuel Joseph M. Bermas - Paul Joshua Dl. Carreon - John Anthony T. Cenon - Neil Fritz C. Ciriaco - Leann B. Sarza', '', 'The thesis presents a College Program Recommender System designed to assist incoming first-year students in selecting suitable college programs. The system used the Random Forest algorithm exclusively for classification purposes, to provide personalized recommendations. The study addresses the challenges faced by grade 12 students in selecting appropriate programs, emphasizing the potential consequences of program mismatch leading to job mismatch in the future. It underscored the necessity for an efficient recommender system to assist students in making informed decisions. The researchers obtained and preprocessed academic data from past students, including course histories, interests, and performance records. They developed and tested the algorithms, revealing that Random Forest successfully captured patterns in academic data, enabling the recommender system to provide credible program suggestions. The accuracy, precision, recall, and F1-score of the algorithms were also assessed to determine their suitability for the task. The study contributes significantly to academic counseling by providing a realistic solution to the issues faced by incoming freshmen during program selection. The test results clearly demonstrate that the Random Forest algorithm achieved 97% accuracy. The findings support the system\'s use of Random Forest to provide accurate and trustworthy program choices for incoming college students, addressing the complexity inherent in academic program selection.', 'College Program Recommendation System, Random Forest, program selection'),
(211, 0, 0, '2024-05', 'BSCS-AD', 'Thesis', 'The Development of E-BASA: An Interactive Reading Application with Implementation of Shuffling Algorithm to Enhance Learning in Filipino Subject', 'Alejandro R. Cerafica Jr. - Kathlyn Mangoba - Fortune Matthew A. Tamares - Elijah Theodore S. Yabut', '', 'This research, \"E-BASA,\" an interactive reading application employing a Shuffling algorithm to enhance Filipino language learning, makes a significant contribution to educational technology by showcasing the effectiveness of personalized apps. This study uses the Shuffling algorithm to create a more personalized and interactive platform. It is a combination of developmental and descriptive evaluative research methods and utilizes the Agile Software Development Life Cycle (SDLC). The evaluation, using the probability metric, shows that the Fisher-Yates algorithm outperforms the linear congruent and Sattolo cycles. Fisher-Yates has the lowest probability of 9.05%, which is the best in terms of the probability that the questions occur, followed by linear congruence (10.48%) and Satollo cycle (11.36%).\nThis paper discusses the problems encountered by E-BASA, gathered through interviews and a pre-survey that allow us to identify user requirements, challenges, and pain points, providing a basis for the development of E-BASA. An evaluation of the system based on the ISO 25010 standards, conducted with 50 respondents, resulted in the second-highest level of agreement, which is \"agree\" on its functional suitability, performance efficiency, flexibility, and interaction capability. Respondents also provided positive feedback on the features, including the pre-test, test creation, classroom creation, and progress report. In conclusion, this study successfully developed an interactive rea', 'Interactive reading application, Shuffling Algorithm, Fisher-Yates Algorithm, Linear Congruence, Sattolo Cycle Algorithm, Probability Metric'),
(212, 0, 0, '2024-05', 'BSIT-NS', 'Capstone', 'Development of Pitch It Perfect: A Mobile Flute Recorder Musical Note Recognition Application Using Convolutional Neural Network Model', 'John Kenneth S. Camarador - Israel Ephraim V. Esteban - Russel John S. Evangelista - Lee Rasheed M. Rebodos', '', 'This research aimed to design and develop an Android application that can detect soprano recorder notes in music, which then can be deployed to help individuals who wish to learn to play music but do not wish to read sheet music. Hence, the researchers developed a Convolutional Neural Network-based Android application for soprano recorder note recognition, which was designed and developed by using Android Studio, Google Firebase, and Retrofit. The Android application classifies musical notes in a piece of music. It displays the label and how it should be performed via an image-based guide that illustrates which Soprano Recorder instrument holes should be covered to play the displayed note. The research design utilized in this investigation is a mixed-method approach, combining quantitative and developmental research methodologies. Given the emphasis on utilizing data, the chosen research methodology for this investigation is the Team Data Science Process (TSDP). This approach allows for a structured and data-driven analysis of the research objectives. The ISO 25010 software quality standard is employed for evaluating the quality of Android applications. The researchers gathered 348 survey responses based on ISO 25010 from two groups of participants: 279 UMak students and 69 Soprano Recorder player UMak students. According to the survey result and the verbal interpretation of responses from UMak students and Soprano Recorder play UMak students, the performance efficiency and p', 'Music Information Retrieval, Neural Networks, Soprano Recorder Instrument, Note Recognition, Convolutional Neural Networks, Android application'),
(213, 0, 0, '2024-05', 'BSCS-AD', 'Thesis', 'The Development of LIB-RO: An Android Mobile and Web Application for Automated Record Keeping in Small Businesses Using Computer Vision OCR Algorithm ', 'Howard G. Bayquen - Atthaleen M. Carlos - Justine Louise T. Carunungan - Raiden V. Guillergan', '', 'Small businesses are important for promoting economic growth in today\'s business environment. However, due to their limited resources and time, a lot of small businesses find it challenging to handle manual bookkeeping techniques. The objective of this project is to automate small business recordkeeping tasks through the development of Lib-Ro, a web and mobile application. Lib-Ro enables the extraction and classification of bills/invoices and receipts into three categories: expense, owner\'s equity, and revenue by utilizing computer vision Optical Character Recognition technology and Artificial Neural Network models. The development involved collaborative efforts with industry partners, including Group Management Corporation, The Benthel Development Corporation, 107 Hub, and 1735 Corporation, who provided support and data for the project. Support vector machines, decision trees, random forest, logistic regression, convolutional neural networks, and gradient boosting with XGBoost were used to assess the neural network. The results showed that the artificial neural network achieved high accuracy, precision, recall, and F1-score of eighty-four percent (84%), eighty-four percent (84%), eighty-four percent (84%), and eighty-three percent (83%) respectively. Evaluation based on ISO/IEC\n25010 standards revealed high ratings for functionality sustainability and reliability, though usability metrics garnered lower scores. Moreover, project evaluation highlighted the app\'s strong perfor', ''),
(214, 0, 0, '2024-05', 'BSIT-NS', 'Capstone', 'FITLIFE PRO: A Web-based Platform Empowering Filipinos to Overcome Barriers and Achieve Health and Wellness Goals', 'Managay, Jenzer Kane M - Garcia, Terenz Gwayn E', '', 'This research paper introduces FitLife Pro, a virtual health and wellness coaching platform aimed at addressing the prevalent challenges individuals face in maintaining optimal health and fitness. With increasing awareness of the importance of physical activity and healthy living, many still struggle due to financial constraints, lack of guidance, time limitations, and motivational barriers. FitLife Pro offers personalized exercise routines, nutritional guidance, and motivational features to empower individuals to take control of their well-being. The project follows a systematic approach, starting with problem definition, research, system design, development, implementation, testing, and evaluation. Leveraging Agile software development methodology, FitLife Pro is designed to meet user needs effectively. It incorporates key features such as personalized workout plans, nutrition guidance, progress tracking, and social networking capabilities. Using Python Flask Framework and Microsoft Azure SQL Database, FitLife Pro ensures scalability, security, and usability. The platform adheres to ISO/IEC 25010:2023 standards, guaranteeing high functionality, reliability, usability, and security. Rigorous testing procedures and pilot testing with a small user group provide valuable feedback for refinement. FitLife Pro aims to revolutionize the health and wellness industry by providing accessible, personalized, and cost-effective solutions. Through continuous evaluation and refinement, it ', 'Health and wellness coaching platform, Health and wellness solutions, FitLife Pro, diet apps'),
(215, 0, 0, '2024-05', 'BSIT-NS', 'Capstone', 'The Development of a Secure Live Streaming Platform with Phishing Attack Resistance for Obanana', 'Ga, James Francis F. - De Torres, Ryan Justine P.', '', 'The developed secure live streaming platform features a digital place where Obanana\'s audience base can interact with each other through activities such as live social engagement and quizzes that earn them points to their wallet. The platform aims to provide Obanana with a realtime web application model that can contribute in expanding their audience base and interactions as a B2C technology company, while implementing security and WebAuthn that provides protection from various phishing attacks as the user attempts to authenticate within the platform, with secure coding practices taken into account. The attacks may include credential stuffing, brute force attacks, session hijacks, SQL injections, XSS, and CSRF, which are known to compromise user accounts and even potentially bypass 2FA methods. The main stack includes Laravel, PHP, JavaScript, NextJS, and WebRTC, deployed as a web application to the cloud. The testing reveals that the developed platform passed the test procedures, performance test (Lighthouse), and security tests (Burp Suite and OWASP ZAP). Evaluation of the platform from client users, IT experts and Obanana employees resulted in highly acceptable ratings across 8 indicators of the ISO/EC 25010 quality assessment framework.\nThe researchers concluded that the developed live streaming platform with phishing resistance is mostly safe, reliable, and easy to use based on the survey conducted.\nThe application has also passed every security test, showing the platfor', 'Application Security, Phishing, WebAuthn, Live streaming, WebRTC, Know Your Customer (KYC) Verification, OWASP Top 10, Common Web Vulnerabilities, Oba'),
(216, 0, 0, '2024-05', 'BSIT-NS', 'Capstone', 'The Development of HIVESTOCK: An Enhanced Solution for the Inventory Management System (IMS) of Nikka Trading', 'Barrameda, Ginalyn M. - Jimenez, Charina M. - Labaniego, Angeline Marie D.', '', 'The capstone project, \"The Development of HiveStock: An Enhanced Solution for the Inventory Management System of Nikka Trading,\" is a direct response to the urgent need for a more effective inventory management system The current system, characterized by manual procedures, obsolete software, and limited visibility, is not only outdated but also poses significant challenges for Nikka Trading. The review of related literature strengthens the proposed study by providing a comprehensive understanding of the current state of knowledge in the field. The study used a descriptive research design to thoroughly examine the project\'s objectives and scope, which involved a comprehensive analysis of existing research on inventory management systems, technological\nadvancements, and recent industry developments. Moreover, the evaluation results with a high rating indicate that the system could meet the following ISO 25010 standards, such as its usability and compatibility. With an average total rating of 3.89, interpreted as \"Acceptable\" in terms of functionality, reliability performance efficiency, usability, compatibility, security, maintainability, and portability. The manual inventory management processes and decentralized spreadsheet reliance further compound the issue, introducing errors and hindering operational efficiency. The proposed solution, a modern inventory management system, offers real-time visibility, streamlined supply chain operations, and strategic integration with core', 'inventory management system, data entry, logistics, technology'),
(217, 0, 0, '2024-05', 'BSIT-NS', 'Capstone', 'Developing an Online Registration System for Mandaluyong College of Science and Technology', 'Dacuycuy, Joseph William G. - Doronila, Denise Claire B.', '', 'Online Registration System is a web-based software application that helps to automate and simplify the process of admitting students into educational institutions such as schools, colleges, and universities. Mandaluyong College of Science and Technology is a newly opened educational institution located in Mandaluyong City, Philippines. This school currently carries out the admissions process manually and faces challenges managing the increasing number of applicants using Google Forms, which raises concerns about data security and PrivaCyThis study aims to develop an Online Registration System for Mandaluyong Cellege of Science and Technology to replace the traditional manual process of registration, and lessen the use load of papers which can be time consuming, prone to errors, and lack adequate security measures. The proposed system offers a secure and user-friendly online registration system with features such as management of contents for administrators, registrar, and end-users for students. This system can help the school automate tasks related to registration, such as managing applications and applicant data. The method used in this study is Agile Methodology. This method is popular in the IT industry known for its adaptability and flexibility in responding to user needs. The evaluation results showed strong agreement with \"4.02 over 5\" rating the system\'s accuracy, functionality, performance efficiency, compatibility, usability, reliability, security, maintainability, ', 'Online Registration System, Mandaluyong College of Science and Technology, Admissions, Registration, Agile Methodology, Authenticated'),
(218, 0, 0, '2024-05', 'BSIT-NS', 'Capstone', 'The Development of Assistech: An Online Help Desk for Municipality of Pateros', 'Ariaga, Bethy Mae S. - Camila, Marlon Cornelio P. - Talagasya, Blesse M.', '', 'Online help desk is implemented in industries to answer inquiries and assist those in need. The Municipality of Pateros struggles to keep up with issues inside the municipality. Considering they have ten barangays with a growing population. the current on-call system might not be reliable since it is prone to altercations. Different departments from the municipality also have concerns that need to be addressed. With those, it can be unorganized and a hassle to deal with. This study aims to develop Assis Tech, an online help desk with an administrator account that can cater to staff and residents\' concerns with their tickets. It also has a chatbot that answers frequently asked questions to minimize the administrator\'s workload and is integrated with two-factor authentication to ensure the system\'s security, preventing unwanted access. This system will increase the municipality\'s accessibility to assist its residents and staff hassle-free, no matter where they are It also allows users to create accounts, which undergo the process of verification by the administrator. Based on the survey conducted by the researchers using ISO 25010 to evaluate the system, IT Professionals, Employees, and Residents gave excellent remarks in each survey category. The researchers successfully developed the system with the features and security integration. This will encourage the Municipality of Pateros to work on issues and concerns in an organized manner. This system will significantly benefit th', 'Online Help Desk, Assis Tech'),
(219, 0, 0, '2024-05', 'BSIT-NS', 'Capstone', 'The Development of Salus: An Electronic Medical Record System Utilizing Advanced Encryption Standard', 'Buenaventura, Ara Beatriz B. - Funa, Princess Richell C. - Santuele, Clyde Lenon A.', '', 'The Electronic Medical Record System (EMRS) represents a cutting-edge digital solution tailored for Taguig Pateros District Hospital and similar healthcare institutions, revolutionizing how patient health records are managed. This system enhances the efficiency of healthcare delivery by digitizing the creation and maintenance of patient records, which are readily accessible to healthcare professionals during consultations. Key features include patient registration, profiling, reports, and appointment scheduling. These functionalities significantly boost operational processes and enhance the overall efficiency of clinical staff. A critical objective of the EMRS is to improve healthcare organizations performance and security. The system employs robust security measures, such as the Advanced Encryption Standard (AES) algorithm, which uses a 256-bit key length to encrypt and decrypt data both in transit and at rest. This ensures the confidentiality and integrity of sensitive patient information. To further protect against web-based threats, the system utilizes Cross-site Request Forgery (CSRF) protection and HTTPonly cookies to secure login requests and safeguard session data. User authentication is fortified through Two-factor Authentication (2FA), which verifies the identity of users, adding an extra layer of security. Additionally, Role-based Access Control (RBAC) is implemented to assign specific authorization levels to users, ensuring that access to sensitive information is ', 'Advanced Encryption Standard, Electronic Medical Records System, Cross-site Request Forgery, HTTPOnly, Role-based Access Control, Audit Trail, Two-fac'),
(220, 0, 0, '2024-05', 'BSIT-NS', 'Capstone', 'Asian Hospital Health Data Hub: Development of Research Information System for Asian Hospital', 'Bueno, Revin R. - Generao, Jonas G. - Mejillano, Bea Bianca R.', '', 'The Hospital Research Information System is a web-based software application tailored for Asian Hospital aimed at modernizing and enhancing the research process within the institution. The Hospital Research Information System aims to digitize and optimize research workflows within Asian Hospital. By leveraging technology, the hospital aims to overcome challenges associated with manual processes. The research design for developing a research information system for Asian Hospital adopts a descriptive approach to address its research process challenges. The study begins with an introduction outlining the need for Enhanced effectiveness and optimized user satisfaction in the research process. A literature review explores successful implementations and challenges faced by similar systems in research settings providing insights to inform the de development process. The study evaluated the web systems functionality, reliability, usability, and security and the results showed that the web system has excellent performance and usability and is reliable and secure. Results of testing reveal that research is reliably recorded and kept in the database and the weBSIT-NSe is compatible with a range of devices and browsers assuring easy accessibility and operation. And lastly, the results of the evaluation that the Asian Hospital Health Data Hub has been effective in addressing the demands of Asian Hospital needs.', 'Hospital Research Information System, Asian Hospital Health Data Hub'),
(221, 0, 0, '2024-05', 'BSIT-NS', 'Capstone', 'Enhancing Business Continuity Through Virtualization: Utilizing Cloud Storage and Sync for Disaster Recovery', 'Joveres, Michelle M. - Malinao, Florence B. - Tan, Charles Vincent D.', '', 'This research synthesizes a network infrastructure design and configuration plan for Obanana Corp, integrating proactive security protocols and industry best practices. By meticulously addressing specific objectives, including the design of local and wide area networks, implementation of AWS services, and integration of disaster recovery measures, the study aims to enhance organizational resilience and operational efficiency. Proactive measures such as firewall security applications and access management protocols ensure robust network security across multiple floors of the PMI Tower. Rigorous testing and validation procedures validate the reliability and performance of the implemented infrastructure, paving the way for a smooth transition and minimal disruption to operations. By adopting these recommendations, Obanana Corp can navigate future technological advancements effectively while safeguarding the integrity and security of its IT infrastructure. Overall, putting these steps into practice will greatly improve Obanana Corp\'s technology setup, ensuring strong security, better day-to-day operations, and a solid base for handling future tech changes.', 'Network Infrastructure, AWS Services, Disaster Recovery, Firewall Security Applications, Network Connection, GNS3, Firewall Configuration, Cloud Infra'),
(222, 0, 0, '2024-05', 'BSIT-NS', 'Capstone', 'Securing Micro Image International Corporation: A Proposed Zero-trust Network Architecture for Data Protection and Risk Mitigation', 'Banaag, Adrian P. - Mamayo, Sittie Janine D. - Vicera, Paul Joshua L.', '', 'This capstone project proposes a comprehensive Zero Trust Network Architecture (ZTNA) solution to strengthen the security posture of Micro Image International Corporation (MIIC). The project addresses the growing security concerns of MIC in light of recent cyber threats. ZTNA significantly improves over traditional perimeter-based security by enforcing continuous authentication of users and devices throughout network sessions. This approach minimizes the potential impact of security breaches by assuming all entities (users, devices, applications) are untrusted. The TNA solution leverages Cisco Duo for multi-factor authentication (MFA), adding an extra layer of security to user logins and restricting unauthorized access. Granular access control further tightens security by limiting access to authorized resources only. The solution also encompasses a secure Wide Area Network (WAN) connection for secure data exchange with sister companies. This WAN connection utilizes Fortinet FortiGate firewalls and Site-to-Site VPN to ensure robust data protection. The firewalls provide additional security features like application control, user authentication, and web filtering. The project recommends a phased approach with user training, security policy reviews, and ongoing threat detection practices to ensure successful implementation. The project also emphasizes the importance of vendor selection and equipment compatibility assessment. By implementing the proposed ZTNA solution and secure ', 'Zero-Trust Network Architecture (ZTNA), Network Security, Data Protection, Micro Image International Corporation (MIIC), Wide Area Network (WAN), Site'),
(223, 0, 0, '2024-05', 'BSIT-NS', 'Capstone', 'A Proposed Enhancement of Network Infrastructure for the City Hall of Trece Martires, with the Implementation of Secured Storage Access', 'Lope, Renz Ivan V. - Lojica, Jericho James M. - Nanong, Jarod Miguel', '', 'The importance of File file-sharing management in any sort of organization comes with the significant tendency to sort information and manage contents within, even today when the methods of compiling files in a cabinet are now digitized. In our everyday use computers for work which makes organizing more efficient and easier to manage. Thus the capstone project entitled \"A PROPOSED ENHANCEMENT OF NETWORK INFRASTRUCTURE FOR THE CITY HALL OF TRECE MARTIRES, WITH THE IMPLEMENTATION OF SECURED STORAGE ACCESS\" uses the hierarchical stacking method for network design to cater to the problem when it comes to downtime in internet connection and utilizing Server 2019, aimed to improve the problem of not having a centralized file sharing management system. This will show the organization\'s effectiveness, efficiency, security, and productivity. It includes the creation of the design network layout, Structured Cabling, applying the security features, and showing the output of the desired solution that will positively improve the overall operation of the organization.\nThe proposed network infrastructure and network security were designed and tested using network simulator software tools such as Cisco Packet Tracer. The organization needs to have these network solutions not just to enhance its network capabilities, but also to solve its problems in terms of internet downtime and security of its network-the incorporation of security features to solve these problems. ISO 25010 was used to eva', 'Server 2019, Hierarchical Model, Security Features, network infrastructure, Centralized file sharing management system.'),
(224, 0, 0, '2024-05', 'BSIT-NS', 'Capstone', 'An Enhanced Wide Area Network Infrastructure for Dost Central Office: Optimized Firewall and System\nNetwork Deployment', 'Canonce, Edrian T. - Delica, Cedric John C. - Lagasca, Kaye M.', '', 'The technology has evolved on how information are exchanged and WANs are the backbone of this interconnected world. However, the complexity of WANS also shows on how organizations expose their security challenges. This research focuses on the development, evaluation and testing of the \"Enhanced Wide Area Network Infrastructure for DOST Central Office: Optimized Firewall and System Network Development. The goal was to design an improved wide-area network infrastructure with VPN, redundancy, scalability, and quality of service control. Employing a Descriptive Approach research design, the research incorporated Likert scales administered to IT Professionals. Positive evaluations from the participants emphasized the proposed network infrastructure\'s satisfactory in terms of functionality, reliability, usability and security. Therefore, the researchers concluded based on the results, that the proposed network infrastructure function works as intended: access switch, core switch, router an d firewall are integrated well. With a total mean score of 4.1 out of 5, the proposed network infrastructure demonstrates that the functionality, reliability and usability of the network infrastructure was rated satisfactory. Overall, these results and findings indicate that the proposed network infrastructure is functional, reliable, usable and secure, making it an effective solution for transferring encrypted data between two DOST branches, offers redundancy, and has a successful connectivity w', 'enhanced wide area network infrastructure, WAN, access switch, core switch, router, firewall, IPSec tunnel, redundancy, scalability, VPN, DOST'),
(225, 0, 0, '2024-05', 'BSIT-NS', 'Capstone', 'Development of a Web-based Sexuality Education Platform for Adolescents', 'Benitez, Trixie May C. - Garcia, Jahmel Andre C. - Gramatica, Julius A', '', 'This paper explores the development and evaluation of a web-based platform for sexuality education, aimed at addressing the lack of comprehensive sexuality education materials in educational institutions. Chapter 1 delves into the background of the issue, highlighting the challenges faced in implementing comprehensive sexuality education in the Philippines. Chapter 2 reviews related literature, providing insights from various studies on sexuality education, online resources, and the effectiveness of web-based programs. In Chapter 5, the study\'s findings, conclusions, and recommendations are presented. The findings indicate that the developed web-based platform performed well in terms of performance efficiency, usability, security, functionality, and maintainability, as evaluated based on ISO 25010 standards. Conclusions drawn from the study emphasize the importance of web-based tools in delivering comprehensive sexuality education and the need for continuous improvement in such platforms. Recommendations include adding a summative test and implementing a certification system to enhance student learning and engagement. Overall, this study contributes to addressing the challenges in providing comprehensive sexuality education through innovative technological solutions.', 'Web-based Sexuality Education, Sexuality Education Platform, Learning Management System'),
(226, 0, 0, '2024-05', 'BSIT-NS', 'Capstone', 'Developing an Online Admission System for Mandalyong College of Science and Technology', 'Balbuena, Ron Alvin O. - Lamadora, Michelle Irish L. - Roc, Roselyn F.', '', 'Online Admission System is a web-based software application that helps to automate and simplify the process of admitting students into educational institutions such as schools, colleges, and universities. Mandalyong College of Science and Technology is a newly opened educational institution located in Mandaluyong City, Philippines. This school currently carries out the admissions process manually and faces challenges managing the increasing number of applicants using Google Forms, which raises concerns about data security and privacy.\nThis study aims to develop an Online Admission System for Mandaluyong College of Science and Technology to replace the traditionally manual process of admission, which can be time-consuming, prone to errors and lacks adequate security measures. The proposed system offers a secure and user-friendly online admission system with features such as content management, data analytics, and two-factor authentication. This system can help the school automate administrative tasks related to admissions, such as managing applications and applicant data. The method used in this study is Agile Methodology. This method is popular in the IT industry known for its adaptability and flexibility in responding to user needs. The evaluation results showed strong agreement with 83.33% rating the system\'s accuracy, ease of use, reliability, and security in managing applications and applicant data. The findings showed that the researchers successfully developed an online', 'Admission System, Online Admission System, Online Examination System'),
(227, 0, 0, '2024-05', 'BSIT-NS', 'Capstone', 'A Proposed Web Application with Cloud-based Security for Integrative Learning Content-based System for Senior High School Students of President Diosda', 'Ormido, John Mark M. - Paz, Jhet Christian V. - Vivo, Sarah Erica D', '', 'This paper helps you understand and know how to develop an online learning management system from the base with the cloud-based security that is reinforced for an additional layer of security for the system which can give peace of mind to the users of the developed project. With the help of the standards that we are utilizing and using nowadays such as AICC, SCORM, xAPI, and cmi5, the developers successfully developed an online learning management system which is for President Diosdado Macapagal High School, this project is addressing the issues of the users of the President Diosdado Macapagal High School like missing requirements, not accurate recordings, missing paper works and many more Based on the of the results and summary of findings that has the researchers gathered from testing and interviews, the performance efficiency, the PDMHS-LMS gets a weighted average mean of 4.21, compatibility testing also gets a staggering value of 4.2 weighted average mean. In terms of usability, the PDMHS-LMS has the weighted average mean of 4.31, lastly, reliability, reliability gets a 4.20 weighted average mean. In conclusion the proposed technology PDMHS-LMS is effective and reliable as an alternative solution for the existing problems that is in the President Diosdado Macapagal High School, with this and backed-up by the research results from the interview and research that the researchers performed', 'Learning management system cloud security, database administrator, ISO 25010, modules, dashboard, web-based application, server, database, switches, t');
