(228, 0, 0, '2024-05', 'BSIT-NS', 'Capstone', 'The Development of a Secure Live Streaming Platform with Phishing Attack Resistance for Obanana', 'Ga, James Francis F. - De Torres, Ryan Justine P.', '', 'The developed secure live streaming platform features a digital place where Obanana\'s audience base can interact with each other through activities such as live social engagement and quizzes that earn them points to their wallet. The platform aims to provide Obanana with a realtime web application model that can contribute in expanding their audience base and interactions as a B2C technology company, while implementing security and WebAuthn that provides protection from various phishing attacks as the user attempts to authenticate within the platform, with secure coding practices taken into account. The attacks may include credential stuffing, brute force attacks, session hijacks, SQL injections, XSS, and CSRF, which are known to compromise user accounts and even potentially bypass 2FA methods. The main stack includes Laravel, PHP, JavaScript, NextJS, and WebRTC, deployed as a web application to the cloud. The testing reveals that the developed platform passed the test procedures, performance test (Lighthouse), and security tests (Burp Suite and OWASP ZAP). Evaluation of the platform from client users, IT experts and Obanana employees resulted in highly acceptable ratings across 8 indicators of the ISO/IEC 25010 quality assessment framework. The researchers concluded that the developed live streaming platform with phishing resistance is mostly safe, reliable, and easy to use based on the survey conducted. The application has also passed every security test, showing the platfo', 'Application Security, Phishing, WebAuthn, Live streaming, WebRTC Know Your Customer (KYC) Verification, OWASP Top 10, Common Web Vulnerabilities, Oban'),
(229, 0, 0, '2024-05', 'BSIT-NS', 'Capstone', 'Development of Bright Byte: A Web-based Application for Teethtalk Dental Clinic', 'Carmona, Sid Nathan F. - Carpio, Elsa P. - Nono, Mark Angelo D.', '', 'The dentistry sector is always striving to enhance its efficiency and care quality. The goal of this study was to create a web application for TeethTalk dental clinic that includes basic dental clinic management system functions like patient information management and easy access to dental/medical history, as well as advanced features like data cleaning and deduplication, data analytics, and two-factor authentication. The application\'s purpose was to identify and eliminate unnecessary entries from the system, as well as improve data quality and accuracy during information display via interactive dashboard visualizations. The research design used by the researchers is design thinking approach which promotes innovation, empathy, and continuous problem-solving, enabling the development of user-centered solutions that effectively address complex challenges. The approach focused on detecting dirty data and duplications that could not be captured by the traditional method used by receptionists and dentists. It is an important approach for cleaning dirty data and identifying duplications, enabling the researchers to identify inaccurate data. The methodology of the study also includes the data flow diagrams as well as the testing and evaluation procedures that will be used to assess the system\'s overall functionality. This study used a diverse strategy to analyze Bright Byte\'s influence on dentistry clinic operations. First, the study investigated the usefulness of data analytics mod', 'data cleaning, data deduplication, data analytics, two-factor authentication'),
(230, 0, 0, '2024-05', 'BSIT-NS', 'Capstone', 'Designing a Scalable and Flexible Network Architecture for Mandaluyong College of Science and Technology with Inter-vlan Routing and Etherchannel Bund', 'Bustillo, Paul Naethan P. - Chua, Julius S. - Rocha, Nathaniel Glenn M.', '', 'As digital technologies rapidly expand, educational institutions must innovate with strong network infrastructures to support diverse academic and administrative activities. This capstone project addresses the unique challenges faced by Mandalyong College of Science and Technology (MCST), a new institution with a direct internet connection. This network setup makes MCST vulnerable to cyberattacks and unreliable internet connections. To address these issues, the researchers proposed a comprehensive network architecture to enhance MCST\'s connectivity, redundancy, scalability, and security. The project focuses on developing a scalable and flexible network infrastructure integrating Inter-VLAN Routing and EtherChannel Bundling Technology, aiming to establish a resilient and adaptable network for current and future needs. Key objectives include optimizing the local area network, vast area network, server management, and network security using tools like Cisco Packet Tracer and GNS3, aligning with ISO 27001:2022 standards. The study used a Likert Scale to evaluate Organizational Control, Physical Control, Technological Control, Redundancy, Scalability, and Reliability, yielding positive results from evaluators. Successful testing validated the proposed project\'s functionality and reliability. This project enhances MCST\'s network infrastructure, providing practical insights and methodologies for newly established institutions. It lays a resilient foundation for the future growth of ', 'Digital Technology, Network Infrastructure, Cyberattacks, Redundancy, Scalability, Inter-VLAN Routing, EtherChannel Bundling, Digital technologies'),
(231, 0, 0, '2024-05', 'BSIT-NS', 'Capstone', 'Enhanced Secured Network with Zero Trust Security and Cloud-Based Backup for the City Hall of Mandaluyong', 'Delerio, Aldwin D. - Quindoza, John Andrew T. - Sasil, Marriel B.', '', 'This proposal suggests comprehensive network infrastructure enhancement to boost the reliability and security of Mandaluyong City Hall\'s network. There are currently weaknesses in the system\'s security, frequent periods of unavailability, and the system cannot be scaled up adequately. To solve these problems, this proposal puts forward many technologies and measures for protection, such as port security, high availability failover, centralized management through Active Directory, more robust security with FortiGate Firewall, and cloud-based backup solutions. These improvements aim to enhance integrity within networks, reduce downtimes, and ensure that critical services continue working at all times without interruptions. The survey findings from the project show that most people agree with the effectiveness and suitability of these changes in their organization\'s structure related to information systems management. According to respondents\' comments about control types introduced by this initiative towards improving security levels while minimizing operational times, it can be concluded that success has been realized in terms of making physical access impossible except for authorized personnel, thus reducing risks emanating from unauthorized entry into buildings housing computers or other sensitive data storage devices used within Mandaluyong. The proposal suggests that the suggested network upgrades be carried out once verified and implemented because they will help improve ', 'Network Infrastructure Enhancement, Security Improvements Reliability, Scalability, Port Security, High Availability Failover, Centralized Management,'),
(232, 0, 0, '2024-05', 'BSIT-NS', 'Capstone', 'Securing Micro Image International Corporation: A Proposed Zero-Trust Network Architecture for Data Protection and Risk Mitigation', 'Banaag, Adrian P. - Mamayo, Sittie Janine D. - Vicera, Paul Joshua L.', '', 'This capstone project proposes a comprehensive Zero Trust Network Architecture (ZTNA) solution to strengthen the security posture of Micro Image International Corporation (MIC). The project addresses the growing security concerns of MIC in light of recent cyber threats. ZTNA significantly improves over traditional perimeter-based security by enforcing continuous authentication of users and devices throughout network sessions. This approach minimizes the potential impact of security breaches by assuming all entities (users, devices, applications) are untrusted. The ZTNA solution leverages Cisco Duo for multi-factor authentication (MFA), adding an extra layer of security to user logins and restricting unauthorized access. Granular access control further tightens security by limiting access to authorized resources only. The solution also encompasses a secure Wide Area Network (WAN) connection for secure data exchange with sister companies. This WAN connection utilizes Fortinet FortiGate firewalls and Site-to-Site VPN to ensure robust data protection. The firewalls provide additional security features like application control, user authentication, and web filtering. The project recommends a phased approach with user training, security policy reviews, and ongoing threat detection practices to ensure successful implementation. The project also emphasizes the importance of vendor selection and equipment compatibility assessment. By implementing the proposed ZTNA solution and secure ', 'Zero-Trust Network Architecture (ZTNA), Network Security, Data Protection, Micro Image International Corporation (MIIC), Wide Area Network (WAN), Site'),
(233, 0, 0, '2024-04', 'BSCS-AD', 'Thesis', 'CST Hub: A Web-based Application System for Style Formatting Analysis of Umak Cs Thesis Manuscript Using Composite Rule-based Algorithm', 'Mhike Laurence N. Laconsay - Henson S. Bunayog - Raphael Jorrel H. Docot - Chastine Joy B. Sanqui - Aia A. Valles', '', 'This study focuses on developing a system for style formatting analysis of UMak CS Thesis Manuscripts using Composite Rule-Based Algorithm by utilizing Python Libraries such as PyMuPDF, and Tesseract OCR. The system consists of calculating bounding boxes to check the formatting of CS thesis papers, providing a valuable tool for students and professors to efficiently review and reduce formatting errors. The method involves calculating PDF paper size, margins, spacings and defining fonts. Using Tesseract OCR and PyMuPDF, the system extracts text details, detects margins, and calculates text spacings. The model detects the errors by highlighting them with OpenCV specifically fonts, margins, and spacing. Despite difficulties in manual data extraction and time-consuming margin and spacing detection, the developed system proves useful in improving UMak CS Thesis Manuscript formatting, resulting with an overall accuracy rate of 90.66% across various formatting components specifically: margin, spacings, and font-related, with a potential for future refinements. Furthermore, the system evaluation reached an overall rating of 3.55, indicating a general acceptance among Computer Science (CS) students and professors.', 'Style Formatting Analysis, Formatting Errors, Composite Rule-based Algorithm, UMak CS Thesis Manuscripts, Text Extraction, Data extraction.='),
(234, 0, 0, '2024-05', 'BSIT-NS', 'Capstone', 'A Web-Based Barangay Resident Information System', 'Araza, Ashley Travis - Catig, Cesar B. Jr - Tobias, Jan Earl M.', '', 'In order to address the difficulty that has been affecting the barangay North Signal in Taguig City, the goal of this study is to offer a solution. The strategy involved developing a digital information system for the barangay to serve as a tool for addressing manual processes. A web-based system known as the Barangay Information System is equipped with functionalities for storing, processing, generating, and managing resident\'s information. The system ensures the security of the system through the implementation of authorization, employing a one-time password (OTP) for additional layer of security to authenticate users during login, ensuring that only the legitimate account holder can perform actions or access sensitive information. Information was properly protected utilizing encryption, decryption and data backup mechanisms, including reCAPTCHA for validating users distinguishing between bots and humans. To develop an information management system, the proponents utilized the PHP programming language. Furthermore, this generate an online backup of the user\'s information to maintain data integrity that assures the information of the users are stored securely within the system. This significantly optimize the management of residence documents and information for Barangay North Signal residents. The research acknowledged that the system has limitations, such as security in biometrics, online transactions, and chatbot. Overall, the research indicates that implementing a web-ba', 'Resident Information System, Web-based, PHP, reCAPTCHA, OneTime Password, Encryption and Decryption, Backup, Digital, North Signal, Taguig City'),
(235, 0, 0, '2024-05', 'BSIT-NS', 'Capstone', 'A Proposed of Secured Wide Area Network Using IPsec Virtual Private Network for Alpha plus Property Holdings Corporation', 'Mariyhela Dennise P. Chan - Bryan Joshua B. Manansala - Mark Edson H. Romarate', '', 'The proposal focused on the enhancement of the network security of Alpha Plus Property Holdings Corporation by implementing a secured Wide Area Network (WAN) using IPsec Virtual Private Network (VPN) technology. The solution involves deploying IPsec VPN for site-to-site and remote access connections, integrating Fortinet security solutions and Google Workspace Business Plus for improved collaboration. The implementation plan includes comprehensive testing to ensure enhanced security, improved performance, and streamlined communication. The proposal aims to provide reliable network infrastructure tailored to the corporation\'s needs, by utilizing VMWare Workstation, Windows Server 2022, Fortinet FortiGate Firewall, and Cisco Packet Tracer. Compliance with ISO/IEC 27001 standards are emphasized to ensure information security and effective risk management, with the deployed network elements serving as crucial protectors of valuable data and enabling authorized access exclusively. The proposed solution will enhance threat detection and incident response, conduct security audits and vulnerability assessments, and improve the overall security and efficiency of Alpha Plus Property Holdings Corporation\'s network infrastructure, thereby reducing the risk of data breaches and cyber-attacks', '(WAN) Wide area network, (IPsec VPN) Internet Protocol Security Virtual Private Network, (ISO/IEC 27001) international standard for information securi'),
(236, 0, 0, '2024-05', 'BSIT-NS', 'Capstone', 'Development of Facilities and Equipment Management System for Barangay Santol', 'Abundo, Precious Apple - Dini-ay, Jonalyn S. - Tusing, Lawrence John P.', '', 'The capstone project titled \"Development of Facilities and Equipment Management System for Barangay Santol\" seeks to revolutionize asset management by addressing the urgent need for an efficient tracking and management system for barangay assets, encompassing buildings, equipment, and vehicles. The primary goal is to design and implement a robust, user-friendly system that empowers barangay officials to monitor assets, schedule maintenance, plan replacements, and optimize resource utilization with precision and ease. Through a thorough analysis, the project identifies existing challenges in the current asset management practices, aiming to not only resolve these issues but also proactively anticipate and mitigate potential risks associated with asset mismanagement, loss, or inefficiencies. Emphasizing user convenience, the system is designed to be intuitive and accessible, ensuring that it meets the practical needs of barangay officials. Integral to the system\'s architecture are stringent access control mechanisms grounded in the CIA Triad principles (Confidentiality, Integrity, and Availability), guaranteeing robust security to protect sensitive data and information input by users, thus fostering a secure and efficient asset management environment for Barangay Santol.', 'Asset inventory management, Threat Mitigation Approach, CIA Triad, Facilities and Equipment.'),
(237, 0, 0, '2024-05', 'BSIT-NS', 'Capstone', 'Sagip Ani: Nurturing Agricultural Prosperity Through an E-commerce Web Application for Marketing Agricultural Products of Pakisama Confederation', 'Malabanan, James B. - Rana Josiah Caleb B. - Saludes, Razia Princess Joy T.', '', 'This study aims to develop a secure web-based e-commerce system for the Pambansang Kilusan ng mga Samahang Magsasaka confederation (PAKISAMA).\nThe system will allow basic e-commerce transactions between customers and admins like purchasing and selling products while securing user data. Asides from the basic features and functionalities that are present on a typical e-commerce system, there are also security features implemented in this study. Security features that are included in this study is Multi-Factor Authentication and bcrypt. Multi-Factor Authentication is a standard security feature implemented on most systems and software applications, it works by verifying the authenticity of a user by requesting a unique one-time pin or OTP sent to their email account upon registering on the system. On the other hand, Bcrypt\'s purpose is to secure data stored in the backend of applications by using a cryptographic hash function that turns a user\'s password into a specific number characters unrecognizable to its original form. The system will be evaluated by using ISO 25010 Product Quality Model Evaluation that assesses a system or software application based on a specific criterion. In this study, the system will be evaluated based on its functionality suitability, interaction capability, reliability, security, and maintainability by three groups. Each group is composed of 10 individuals which are e-commerce platform users, PAKISAMA employees, and IT specialists. The results of the', 'Agriculture, E-commerce, Web Application, Bcrypt, PAKISAMA Confederation, Bcrypt, Security'),
(238, 0, 0, '2024-05', 'BSIT-NS', 'Capstone', 'A Proposed Web Application with Cloud-based Security for Integrative Learning Content-based\nSystem for Senior High School Students of President Diosda', 'Ormido, John Mark M. - Paz, Jhet Christian V. -  Vivo, Sarah Erica D', '', 'This paper helps you understand and know how to develop an online learning management system from the base with the cloud-based security that is reinforced for an additional layer of security for the system which can give peace of mind to the users of the developed project. With the help of the standards that we are utilizing and using nowadays such as AICC, SCORM, xAPI, and cmi5, the developers successfully developed an online learning management system which is for President Diosdado Macapagal High School, this project is addressing the issues of the users of the President Diosdado Macapagal High School like missing requirements, not accurate recordings, missing paper works and many more. Based on the of the results and summary of findings that has the researchers gathered from testing and interviews, the performance efficiency, the PDMHS-LMS gets a weighted average mean of 4.21, compatibility testing also gets a staggering value of 4.2 weighted average mean. In terms of usability, the PDMHS-LMS has the weighted average mean of 4.31, lastly, reliability, reliability gets a 4.20 weighted average mean. In conclusion the proposed technology PDMHS-LMS is effective and reliable as an alternative solution for the existing problems that is in the President Diosdado Macapagal High School, with this and backed-up by the research results from the interview and research that the researchers performed', 'Learning management system, cloud security, database, administrator, ISO 25010, modules, dashboard, web-based application, server, database, switches,'),
(239, 0, 0, '2024-05', 'BSIT-NS', 'Capstone', 'Development of Propertease: \"A Property Information and Security Management System\"', 'Chavez, Jan Axcel V. - Garcia, Mary Joyce D. - Garcia, Shaine Marie C.', '', 'The real estate industry faces significant challenges in managing their property-related data. Golden Home Realty relies merely on spreadsheets, which are vulnerable and prone to human errors and Data breaches. As a result of manual input can have severe consequences, underscoring the critical importance of information security. In response, the development of PropertEASE: \"A property information and security management system\" emerges as a robust web application designed to address these complexities, and it ensures information confidentiality and privacy through multi-factor authentication via email verification, data encryption and system with its database for more secure data storage and quick and easy navigation, allowing them to manage their property information and security more efficiently. The development process involves phases such as planning, system design, development, testing, deployment, and ongoing maintenance. By adhering to these phases, PropertEASE aims to create a robust property information and security management system that meets user needs and delivers value. PropertEASE promises to benefit everyone in the real estate game. Golden Home Realty Dev. Inc. can streamline data management, employees can be more productive, and property owners gain peace of mind. Buyers, sellers, and tenants all win with accurate information and a smoother transaction process. By prioritizing trust and reliability, PropertEASE has the potential to revolutionize the real esta', 'Information Security Management System, PropertEASE Management.'),
(240, 0, 0, '2024-05', 'BSIT-NS', 'Capstone', 'An Enhanced Wide Area Network Infrastructure for Dost Central Office: Optimized Firewall and System Network Deployment', 'Canonce, Edrian T. - Delica, Cedric John C. - Lagasca, Kaye M.', '', 'The technology has evolved on how information are exchanged and WANs are the backbone of this interconnected world. However, the complexity of WANs also shows on how organizations expose their security challenges. This research focuses on the development, evaluation and testing of the \"Enhanced Wide Area Network Infrastructure for DOST Central Office: Optimized Firewall and System Network Development\". The goal was to design an improved wide-area network infrastructure with VPN, redundancy, scalability, and quality of service control. Employing a Descriptive Approach research design, the research incorporated Likert scales administered to IT Professionals. Positive evaluations from the participants emphasized the proposed network infrastructure\'s satisfactory in terms of functionality, reliability, usability and security. Therefore, the researchers concluded based on the results, that the proposed network infrastructure function works as intended: access switch, core switch, router and firewall are integrated well. With a total mean score of 4.1 out of 5, the proposed network infrastructure demonstrates that the functionality, reliability and usability of the network infrastructure was rated satisfactory. Overall, these results and findings indicate that the proposed network infrastructure is functional, reliable, usable and secure making it an effective solution for transferring encrypted data between two DOST branches, offers redundancy, and has a successful connectivity wi', 'enhanced wide area network infrastructure, WAN, access switch, core switch, router, firewall, IPSec tunnel, redundancy, scalability, VPN, DOST'),
(241, 0, 0, '2024-05', 'BSIT-NS', 'Capstone', 'Univizit: Development of Web-Based Visitor Management System at the University of Makati', 'Espares, Roi Dominic R. - Guillermo, Kristen Julien M. - Tomas, Mary Joy D.', '', 'Real-time systems in today\'s Computer Technology are very important, and as businesses navigate an Ever-Changing Environment, IT now plays a vital part in designing and improving management systems. The University of Makati was established in 1972, with the envisioned school as an instrument that provides University Education to mold Makati youth as productive citizens. School Safety and Security is crucial for the University to secure important information or data of employee staff and especially the Professors and Students. On top of that, to secure and protect all the technologies, which are the devices of the Professors and Students inside the University. In colleges and universities, the lack of an efficient visitor management system presents a worrying vulnerability, resulting in the unauthorized entry of intruders who may take advantage of the surveillance gap to steal valuable assets. To address the issue, the developers suggest digitizing the visitor handling process and making it more effective with a Web-App that is not only accessible on the Internet but is also responsive to mobile devices To Develop a web-based application with Super Admin, Admin, and Visitors as the Main Users. However, in the system, there is a Privileged Account that can create admin accounts, print records of Visitor Information, and have an Auto Archive in their Dashboard. Admin Accounts with Little Privilege such as decrypting the visitor\'s information and approval of the Registration. The', 'School Safety, Visitor Management System, Web-Based Visitor Management System'),
(242, 0, 0, '2024-05', 'BSIT-NS', 'Capstone', 'Rise and Thrive: A Web-Based Platform to Promote Kalinga Culture, Products, and Services', 'Ariaga, Ma. Angelica C. - Collado, Mariecolle G. - Lineses, Kenneth O. - Piojo, Rainlyn', '', 'In an age marked by digital connectivity and global trade, the potential of e-commerce to uplift marginalized communities is evident. This study focuses on the development of an e-commerce platform for the indigenous population of Kalinga, Philippines, aimed at promoting their rich cultural heritage and empowering their economic endeavors. The proposed platform, Rise and Thrive, seeks to address the challenges faced by indigenous entrepreneurs, including limited market access and authenticity issues, by providing a dedicated marketplace with features designed to prioritize authenticity, cultural significance, and data security. The significance of this research lies in its pioneering launch of an e-commerce platform tailored specifically for the indigenous population of Kalinga, Philippines. it is for economic empowerment and cultural preservation, the platform offers Kalinga immediate benefits in expanding market reach and connecting with a global audience. By fostering sales growth and positioning Kalinga as a cultural hub, the platform attracts tourism and reinforces the authenticity of indigenous offerings, aside from that it uses technologies such as PHP, HTML, CSS, JavaScript, and MySQL, the platform incorporates measures in security and a payment method to ensure user confidence. Testing and evaluation based on ISO 25010 criteria ensure the platform\'s functionality and adherence to standards of confidentiality, integrity, non-repudiation, and accountability. The study\'', 'Kalinga, E-Commerce, Indigenous Products, Kalinga Culture,Indigenous WeBSIT-NSe');
